1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,336
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:07,215
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,508 --> 00:00:10,677
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:19,561
[Dmitri] <i>Maybe you'd want to look</i>
<i>for Janine's father.</i>

7
00:00:19,644 --> 00:00:20,687
[Audrey] <i>What for, Dad?</i>

8
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:23,606
<i>I'm sure wherever he is,</i>
<i>he's already happy.</i>

9
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:25,108
He has his own life now.

10
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:29,529
[emcee, in English]
2026 Little Miss Primary School!

11
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:30,780
[audience cheering]

12
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:31,823
Ibyang!

13
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:33,908
[in English] My name is Janine Ranoy,

14
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:38,371
and I am here to show each
and every one of you perfection!

15
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:40,498
[in English] And I thank you!

16
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:43,209
[Ibyang] <i>This is my first time</i>
<i>joining something like this.</i>

17
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:45,295
I am already excited to…

18
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:48,131
experience everything for the first time!

19
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:49,924
[audience cheering] Ibyang!

20
00:00:50,008 --> 00:00:52,510
I will make sure that Ibyang loses.

21
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:53,511
[girl] <i>Ibyang.</i>

22
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:55,305
You got dirt on your face.

23
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:56,222
[Jannie] <i>Here, wipe it off.</i>

24
00:00:57,932 --> 00:00:59,434
What… What happened to Ibyang?

25
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:00,769
[audience jeering]

26
00:01:00,852 --> 00:01:01,811
PREVIOUSLY

27
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:02,771
- [Atoy] <i>What happened?</i>
- [Tonet] <i>Come down, Ibyang.</i>

28
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:03,897
<i>Let her down!</i>

29
00:01:03,980 --> 00:01:05,940
- I'll clean her face.
- Wait. Hold on.

30
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:07,108
[Martina, in English]
<i>What's happening with her face?</i>

31
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:08,193
[Dmitri, in English] <i>I don't know.</i>

32
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:10,653
Maybe that's part of her performance.

33
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:12,614
[Ibyang] <i>I don't want to dance anymore.</i>

34
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:14,991
I'll just go home.

35
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:16,659
[music fades]

36
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:19,621
[audience jeering]

37
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:22,165
Ibyang,

38
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:23,708
do the dance again.

39
00:01:25,418 --> 00:01:28,588
Master, what happened to your face?

40
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:32,217
Well then, we're the same.
It's a tie. Right?

41
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,510
Come on.

42
00:01:33,593 --> 00:01:35,094
Let's dance. I'll join you.

43
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:37,514
Even if we have blue paint on our faces?

44
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:39,140
Yes. So what?

45
00:01:39,224 --> 00:01:40,058
If they laugh at you,

46
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:41,935
then they'll laugh at me too!

47
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:44,145
As long as I'm with you,
let's do this together.

48
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:47,774
- Do you know the steps, Master?
- Yes.

49
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:50,026
Only Sis Tonet and I know the steps.

50
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:52,237
I watched you and Tonet.

51
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,488
I know the steps. I got this!

52
00:01:53,571 --> 00:01:55,657
You do your thing. Just back me up!

53
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,325
No, I'll be your backup.

54
00:01:57,408 --> 00:01:58,868
- Okay? Let's go!
- Yeah.

55
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:00,662
She's okay to dance now.

56
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:06,626
- [in English] Let's welcome our contestant
- [Atoy] There it is.

57
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:07,836
- from Grade 1!
- [Atoy] Get ready.

58
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:10,255
- Ivy Santos!
- [Atoy] We can do this. Let's go!

59
00:02:10,338 --> 00:02:11,798
[cheering]

60
00:02:11,881 --> 00:02:13,049
Ibyang!

61
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:15,135
Whoo! Go, Ibyang!

62
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:16,678
[audience cheering]

63
00:02:16,761 --> 00:02:17,679
[Karla] Ibyang!

64
00:02:17,762 --> 00:02:19,973
- [audience cheering]
- [upbeat music playing]

65
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:21,224
[Karla] Go, Ibyang!

66
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:22,392
[audience cheering]

67
00:02:37,448 --> 00:02:39,659
Even if she's joined by her fake father,

68
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,369
it's still useless.

69
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:44,247
Look, people are still laughing at her.

70
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:45,498
[Janine cackles]

71
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:46,958
[audience cheering]

72
00:02:55,550 --> 00:03:00,471
[sentimental music playing]

73
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:21,034
- [audience cheering]
- [upbeat music playing]

74
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:22,744
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

75
00:03:22,827 --> 00:03:24,913
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

76
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:26,789
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

77
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:30,668
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

78
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:34,255
You're so good, Atoy!

79
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,554
[Tonet, in English] Go, Atoy, my love! Oh.

80
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:43,932
Ibyang! Go, Ibyang!

81
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:49,479
‪[cheering]

82
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:52,941
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

83
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:54,817
Ibyang! Ibyang!

84
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:56,110
Ibyang! Ibyang!

85
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,112
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

86
00:03:58,196 --> 00:03:59,739
Ibyang! Ibyang!

87
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:01,658
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

88
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:04,786
Why do people still seem so delighted
with Ibyang's dance?

89
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:11,709
Annoying.

90
00:04:14,796 --> 00:04:16,339
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang!

91
00:04:16,422 --> 00:04:18,007
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

92
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,884
Ibyang! Ibyang!

93
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,803
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

94
00:04:21,886 --> 00:04:23,680
Ibyang! Ibyang!

95
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:25,598
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

96
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:26,933
Ibyang! Ibyang!

97
00:04:27,016 --> 00:04:29,018
[both exclaim]

98
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:31,604
[chanting] Ibyang! Ibyang!

99
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:34,816
[exclaims]

100
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:39,696
[sentimental music playing]

101
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:40,613
‪[chanting continues]

102
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:44,993
[exclaims]

103
00:04:46,744 --> 00:04:48,288
[Karla] Go, Ibyang!

104
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:51,124
‪[audience cheering]

105
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:54,919
[Karla] Ibyang!

106
00:04:59,048 --> 00:05:00,633
[Karla] Go, Ibyang!

107
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:02,468
[audience cheering]

108
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:04,053
[Ame] Atoy is so hot!

109
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:06,764
[Karla] Go, Ibyang!

110
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:09,225
[audience cheering]

111
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:11,227
[Ame] Go, Ibyang!

112
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:19,110
‪[cheering, applause]

113
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:22,071
[Karla] Go, Ibyang!

114
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:24,157
[elated chuckle] That's my child!

115
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:25,950
‪Oops, never mind.

116
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:27,410
[Tonet giggling]

117
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:54,771
[music fades]

118
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:59,984
[sauve theme music playing]

119
00:06:04,363 --> 00:06:05,323
[snipping]

120
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:12,580
[gunshots blasting]

121
00:06:12,663 --> 00:06:14,874
[clicking]

122
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:16,959
[snipping]

123
00:06:18,002 --> 00:06:20,088
[electronic blipping]

124
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:25,635
[Atoy chuckles]

125
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:28,554
I don't know how I did that!

126
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,973
Well, of course, you're very good!

127
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:34,352
It seems my performance turned out better.

128
00:06:34,977 --> 00:06:36,896
Thank you, Master.

129
00:06:36,979 --> 00:06:38,606
You're the best!

130
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:40,775
Oh? That was all you.

131
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:43,444
Wait. How did you end up
with paint on your face?

132
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:45,196
You really like paint, huh?

133
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:46,155
The first time you painted,

134
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:48,699
you got yellow paint on your clothes.

135
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:51,369
Now, you have blue paint on your face.

136
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:52,995
What happened there?

137
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,664
[pensive music playing]

138
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:57,708
You and Sis Tonet
were talking to me earlier,

139
00:06:57,792 --> 00:06:59,919
before I went up on the stage.

140
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,296
Things were going fine then.

141
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:05,091
Ibyang.

142
00:07:05,174 --> 00:07:06,384
You got dirt on your face.

143
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:07,635
- Ah, yes.
- Really?

144
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:09,512
And then…

145
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:12,223
Janine came closer to me

146
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:13,975
and one of her friends too.

147
00:07:14,058 --> 00:07:15,268
Here, wipe it off.

148
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:16,727
- [Ibyang] Okay.
- [Janine] That's embarrassing.

149
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:18,521
[student] Fix your makeup first.

150
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:20,481
Here too. Do it like this.

151
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:22,233
[suspicious music playing]

152
00:07:22,316 --> 00:07:23,484
On the nose, on the nose.

153
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,530
Why?

154
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:29,407
Did she do something to you?

155
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:30,783
Did they do something to you?

156
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,660
[music intensifies]

157
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:35,455
[exclaims] Oh! You're really
very good, Ibyang!

158
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:37,665
High five! Atoy, you're amazing.

159
00:07:37,748 --> 00:07:40,209
Wow, your performance was truly the best.

160
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:41,878
Oh, thank you!

161
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:43,421
[Tonet] Oh, come on now.

162
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:45,047
I feel like we need to clean your face,

163
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,340
because Q and A is next.

164
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:47,758
- All right, all right,
- I'll wash my face too.

165
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:48,676
- Go, go, go, go, go!
- [exclaims]

166
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:51,262
Good day.

167
00:07:51,345 --> 00:07:54,474
I am a child who was left by her mother.

168
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:02,773
Mom, why did you leave me?

169
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:04,984
Was my embrace not enough?

170
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,238
I've been waiting by the window for days,

171
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:11,991
but only the wind comes.

172
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:13,659
[optimistic music playing]

173
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:16,704
Sometimes, I'm all alone

174
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:19,540
with my beloved teddy bear,

175
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:23,711
who is the only one who calls me "dear".

176
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:27,757
But now, I will not cry anymore.

177
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:30,301
Because someday,

178
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:34,555
I know I will become
a beauty queen in the future,

179
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:37,016
and when you see me on TV,

180
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:38,893
I know what you will say.

181
00:08:39,477 --> 00:08:40,353
"That's my child."

182
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:44,065
[music concludes]

183
00:08:44,815 --> 00:08:46,651
[in English] Solid performance!

184
00:08:46,734 --> 00:08:48,903
- She's my grandchild!
- [in English] Yes.

185
00:08:48,986 --> 00:08:50,071
Really?

186
00:08:50,571 --> 00:08:51,697
Her performance was horrible.

187
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:53,908
- It's obvious she's trying too hard.
- Yes.

188
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:55,243
- Keep quiet.
- [sneaky music playing]

189
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:56,202
[in English] Oh, I'm sorry,

190
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:58,120
if you can't appreciate art like this.

191
00:08:58,204 --> 00:09:00,581
I'm sure you don't know anything
about the West End.

192
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:01,791
What did she say?

193
00:09:04,168 --> 00:09:07,880
[sneaky music playing]

194
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:13,344
[music fades]

195
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:18,099
There! All good.

196
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:20,268
Go to Atoy over there.

197
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:22,895
He's at our table.
I'll just wash my hands.

198
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:24,605
- Okay.
- [Tonet] Are you okay?

199
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:25,773
Mmm-hmm.

200
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:29,860
[dark tense music playing]

201
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:43,708
Are you proud of what you did, Janine?

202
00:09:45,876 --> 00:09:48,170
Ah, sorry. What are you saying?

203
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:51,757
Ah! Okay, my monologue?

204
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:54,176
Of course, I practiced that for hours.

205
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,598
You're really a liar, aren't you?

206
00:09:58,681 --> 00:09:59,515
[Janine] Hmm.

207
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:02,518
Wh-why? I'm just sitting here quietly.

208
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:05,563
Go ahead. Keep lying.

209
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:10,109
We both know you're the one
who put blue paint on my face.

210
00:10:10,192 --> 00:10:11,902
Don't accuse me!

211
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:15,740
- [tense sinister music playing]
- [groans]

212
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:19,035
Ibyang, what are you doing to Janine?!

213
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:20,745
‪[music intensifies]

214
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:26,125
Mommy, I don't know why she pushed me.

215
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:30,171
Why did you do that, Ibyang?

216
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:32,590
What did Janine ever do to you?

217
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:36,260
She's the one
who put blue paint on my face.

218
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,305
- Eh--
- [stutters]

219
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:41,641
How did you know that, huh?

220
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:42,892
Can you prove it?

221
00:10:45,269 --> 00:10:48,731
Ibyang, I know you
and my daughter are enemies.

222
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:50,816
But that doesn't mean

223
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,568
you should always blame her

224
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,403
whenever something bad happens to you.

225
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:56,864
But it's true!

226
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:02,536
And she was the one who pushed me first.

227
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:04,497
That's not true, Mommy.

228
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:07,500
I was just sitting quietly here, and then…

229
00:11:08,084 --> 00:11:10,127
Ibyang suddenly pushed me.

230
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:13,798
[pensive music playing]

231
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:16,217
You're such a liar!

232
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:18,135
In front of your mommy?
Aren't you ashamed?

233
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:20,096
[in English] That's enough, Ibyang.

234
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:23,766
Apologize to Janine.

235
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,310
I will not apologize to her!

236
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:27,395
[tense music playing]

237
00:11:27,478 --> 00:11:29,563
I know she's the one responsible for that.

238
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:32,566
She should be the one apologizing to me.

239
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:34,068
She's a bad child!

240
00:11:34,151 --> 00:11:35,194
[in English] Stop it!

241
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:36,904
[dramatic stinging]

242
00:11:43,577 --> 00:11:44,995
[stutters] I'm…

243
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:46,747
[in English] I'm-I'm so sorry, Ibyang.
I'm-I'm…

244
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:50,000
I'm so sorry for raising my voice at you.

245
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:53,170
[somber music playing]

246
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:54,630
I'm really sorry.

247
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:57,258
[Jannie] Mommy, don't apologize to her.

248
00:11:57,341 --> 00:11:59,176
I'm the one who got hurt.

249
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,719
Come on, Janine. Let's go!

250
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:04,640
Ibyang, please.

251
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:06,934
I hope this is the last time.

252
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:08,853
[in English] Please.

253
00:12:10,312 --> 00:12:11,605
Stay away from my daughter.

254
00:12:15,734 --> 00:12:17,111
[in English] Let's go, Janine.

255
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:34,044
Thank you.

256
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:36,630
You removed the makeup from my face.

257
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:38,174
You're such a show-off.

258
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:39,967
You even had it removed,

259
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:42,386
when you looked so cute earlier.

260
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:44,847
And you and Ibyang looked
so cute on stage.

261
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:46,932
You really looked
like father and daughter.

262
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:47,850
Hmm?

263
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:51,103
Thank you too, because if not for you,
she wouldn't have been able to perform.

264
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,521
Good thing you found a way.

265
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:55,065
Actually, if it weren't for you,

266
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:57,985
this might have been
a traumatic experience for Ibyang.

267
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:01,655
Oh, ah--

268
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:02,573
Oh, Ibyang!

269
00:13:02,656 --> 00:13:03,657
What's the problem?

270
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:06,702
[Ibyang] Nothing.

271
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:10,122
Ibyang, what really happened
to you earlier?

272
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:12,625
Why did you end up
with paint on your face, huh?

273
00:13:15,002 --> 00:13:17,296
Let's not think about that anymore.

274
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:21,842
What matters is that I'm happy
that I was still able to perform,

275
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:23,219
and that I was with you.

276
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:27,890
You're the best!

277
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:29,391
[Tonet] Hmm.

278
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:32,853
No. You're the best because…

279
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:35,314
you're the fruit of the love
between Atoy and me.

280
00:13:35,397 --> 00:13:36,357
‪[quirky sting]

281
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:38,734
Oops! No, that was just a joke.
Just a joke.

282
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:41,946
What I mean is, Atoy and I love you.

283
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:44,406
[bright music playing]

284
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:45,366
[Tonet] Hmm!

285
00:13:57,461 --> 00:13:59,421
[sighs] Me too, I'll join in.

286
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:05,344
Janine, why do you want
to win this beauty pageant?

287
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,722
[in English] Thank you for that question.

288
00:14:09,723 --> 00:14:12,601
For me, I want to win because

289
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:16,981
my Mommy and I really
prepared hard for this pageant,

290
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:19,441
and I believe that

291
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,944
when you work hard for something,

292
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:23,946
you deserve to win more.

293
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:26,574
That's why I'm really giving my best here,

294
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:29,076
my 101%!

295
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:30,953
[in English] And I thank you!

296
00:14:31,036 --> 00:14:32,121
Wow.

297
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:34,290
- [laughs]
- [indistinct chatter]

298
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:35,916
[Dmitri, in English] Very good answer.

299
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,209
[in English] Very good.

300
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:38,127
‪[laughs]

301
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:41,171
[emcee, in English] Good answer!

302
00:14:41,255 --> 00:14:43,090
Thank you, Janine!

303
00:14:43,173 --> 00:14:46,302
[in English] Last but not least,
from Grade 1,

304
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:49,138
Ivy Santos!

305
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:50,347
[cheering]

306
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:52,558
You can do it, Ibyang!

307
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:57,062
[Karla] Your Sis Ame taught you!

308
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:58,522
[emcee, in English] Okay.

309
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:00,691
This is from Mrs. Suarez,

310
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:03,068
adviser from Grade 6.

311
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:06,614
What is the most beautiful gift

312
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:09,992
you received from your parents?

313
00:15:11,619 --> 00:15:15,080
[somber music playing]

314
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:19,835
The truth is…

315
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:23,047
I don't have parents.

316
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:25,424
I grew up in an orphanage.

317
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:32,097
But now, Master Atoy and Sis Tonet

318
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:34,558
stand as my parents.

319
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:38,479
[sentimental music playing]

320
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:41,941
And that, I think,

321
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:45,903
is the most beautiful gift they gave me,

322
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,198
to accompany me in this contest

323
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:51,617
because they love me,

324
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:53,869
and they are proud of me.

325
00:15:54,995 --> 00:15:56,622
That's all. Thank you.

326
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:58,582
[audience cheering, clapping]

327
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:00,334
Go, Ibyang!

328
00:16:00,417 --> 00:16:03,420
You're amazing!

329
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:04,421
[Ame] Go, Ibyang!

330
00:16:05,172 --> 00:16:06,548
[invigorating music playing]

331
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:08,634
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

332
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:11,053
Ibyang! Ibyang!

333
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:14,515
We really raised our child well, Atoy,
didn't we?

334
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:15,933
‪[quirky sting]

335
00:16:21,689 --> 00:16:23,107
She really makes us proud, right?

336
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:24,775
[titters]

337
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:33,075
[audience applauding]

338
00:16:39,164 --> 00:16:42,751
- [quirky sting]
- [chuckles]

339
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:44,920
I cried because of our child.

340
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,885
There-- [chuckles softly]

341
00:16:55,347 --> 00:16:58,809
[principal, in English] For Best Gown,
Anaiah Ong!

342
00:16:58,892 --> 00:17:02,104
[applauding]

343
00:17:03,605 --> 00:17:08,027
[epic music playing]

344
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:14,867
[principal, in English] And now,
for our Best Performance.

345
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:16,618
We had a bit of difficulty here,

346
00:17:16,702 --> 00:17:19,121
because the kids were all really amazing.

347
00:17:19,204 --> 00:17:22,958
But we need to give this
to Ms. Axle Eliseo

348
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:25,836
for her beautiful painting earlier!

349
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:30,632
That painting was… unique.

350
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:35,471
[applauding]

351
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:41,977
[principal, in English]
For the Crowd Favorite award,

352
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:45,856
let's call on Ms. Ivy Santos!

353
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:50,027
[exclaiming and cheering]

354
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,613
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang!

355
00:17:52,696 --> 00:17:55,949
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

356
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:58,494
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

357
00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:01,121
Thank you!

358
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:03,957
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

359
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:07,336
Ibyang! Ibyang!

360
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:09,088
Ibyang! Ibyang!

361
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:11,799
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

362
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:16,136
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

363
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:19,932
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

364
00:18:20,015 --> 00:18:21,683
We love you, Ibyang!

365
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:25,771
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

366
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:28,482
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

367
00:18:28,565 --> 00:18:31,068
[whooping and cheering]

368
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:39,159
[principal, in English] And now,
for the most prestigious award of all,

369
00:18:39,243 --> 00:18:41,245
to be crowned by last year's winner,

370
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:43,497
Anica Belardo,

371
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:47,417
our 2026 Little Miss Primary School…

372
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:51,421
[heartbeat thumping sound]

373
00:18:53,006 --> 00:18:55,509
Ms. Janine Ranoy!

374
00:18:55,592 --> 00:18:56,802
Yes! [laughs]

375
00:18:57,344 --> 00:18:58,720
That's my grandchild!

376
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,222
[applauding]

377
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:01,765
[epic music playing]

378
00:19:01,849 --> 00:19:03,100
Yay!

379
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:04,268
[in English] Get up!

380
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:10,232
[applauding]

381
00:19:18,866 --> 00:19:19,700
[applauding]

382
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:38,844
[softly] Okay.

383
00:19:39,678 --> 00:19:40,971
[smooches]

384
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:42,264
[smooches]

385
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:46,602
- [audience] Ibyang! Ibyang!
- Wait, wait, wait!

386
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:48,645
Before anything else! I just want to say,

387
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:50,063
Atoy is really good at dancing.

388
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:51,857
[exclaiming and laughing]

389
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:52,858
Atoy! Atoy!

390
00:19:52,941 --> 00:19:54,902
One more! One more!

391
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:57,029
[exclaiming and teasing]

392
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:58,405
[chuckles] No!

393
00:19:58,488 --> 00:20:02,159
But the best part really was the Q and A!

394
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:04,244
[exclaiming and applauding]

395
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:05,412
It was so much fun,

396
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:07,164
- even if you didn't win, baby!
- You were really amazing

397
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:08,624
at answering, Ibyang!

398
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:09,791
[exclaiming and applauding]

399
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,335
I take after you, Sis Ame!

400
00:20:11,418 --> 00:20:12,419
[Ame giggles]

401
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:13,921
It was so much fun,

402
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:15,214
even if you didn't win, baby.

403
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:16,590
You're the favorite of the whole school,

404
00:20:16,673 --> 00:20:17,883
and of your teachers too!

405
00:20:17,966 --> 00:20:22,221
[exclaiming and applauding]

406
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:25,849
It's okay even though I didn't win,

407
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:29,937
- because the whole experience was so fun!
- [Tonet] Wow!

408
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,271
[exclaiming and applauding]

409
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:34,441
See! Even after Q and A,
she's still great at answering!

410
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:36,151
You're really awesome!

411
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,904
My idol! You're my idol!

412
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:41,448
Because of that, let's do a group hug

413
00:20:41,531 --> 00:20:42,532
- for Ibyang!
- [all] Group hug!

414
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:43,784
[Tonet] Group hug! Group hug!

415
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,202
Group hug! Group hug!

416
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:46,995
[lively chattering]

417
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:48,205
[all] Group hug! Group hug!

418
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:50,332
- Group hug! Group hug! Group hug!
- [woman exclaims]

419
00:20:50,874 --> 00:20:51,959
[all cheer]

420
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:53,961
[woman] You're the winner for us!

421
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:55,170
You're the winner!

422
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:58,924
[Tonet] Oh, picture! Let's take a picture!

423
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:01,301
Picture, picture. Let's take a picture.
Picture, picture.

424
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:02,970
[Paldo] The barangay captain goes first!

425
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:04,054
[exclaiming and teasing]

426
00:21:04,137 --> 00:21:05,639
[overlapping] Me, me first.

427
00:21:05,722 --> 00:21:07,266
You pose there in the middle!

428
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:09,101
[lively chattering]

429
00:21:10,018 --> 00:21:11,770
Can't the family go first?

430
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:13,689
[lively chattering]

431
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:16,775
- [Cita] Tonet! Here, Tonet!
- [in English] Congratulations, Janine.

432
00:21:16,858 --> 00:21:17,985
[in English] Very well done.

433
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:20,195
[in English] Well deserved, Janine.

434
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:21,363
[in English] Congratulations!

435
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:23,615
[Audrey, in English] Uh,
let's take a group photo!

436
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:25,909
- [in English] All right! Okay.
- [Martina] Okay.

437
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:26,952
[in English] Okay.

438
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:29,371
[somber music playing]

439
00:21:29,454 --> 00:21:30,831
[Audrey, in English] Smile!

440
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:37,838
[exclaiming and applauding]

441
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:40,549
[in English] Beautiful.

442
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:42,384
[mellow music playing]

443
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:45,053
[Martina, in English] You look so pretty!

444
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:46,805
[Audrey, in English]
Can't wait to display this.

445
00:21:46,888 --> 00:21:48,015
[group exclaiming]

446
00:21:48,098 --> 00:21:50,142
[all] Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

447
00:21:50,225 --> 00:21:54,771
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!
Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

448
00:21:54,855 --> 00:21:55,939
Let's go, dear?

449
00:21:57,024 --> 00:21:58,442
- [in English] Come on.
- [in English] Let me help you with that.

450
00:22:02,654 --> 00:22:03,864
[thuds softly]

451
00:22:05,282 --> 00:22:08,994
[mellow music playing]

452
00:22:17,044 --> 00:22:18,170
Oh, son of a thread!

453
00:22:18,253 --> 00:22:20,213
[chuckles]

454
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:21,673
You startled me, Master!

455
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:24,092
[chuckles] Sorry about that.

456
00:22:24,801 --> 00:22:25,886
So? Did you enjoy?

457
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:27,888
[in English] Enjoy?

458
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:30,974
Master, it feels like this is…

459
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:33,435
the best day of my life!

460
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,020
Oh…

461
00:22:36,229 --> 00:22:37,564
It's true!

462
00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:40,984
Especially when I found out

463
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,445
you went to the contest

464
00:22:43,528 --> 00:22:45,864
instead of going to your job.

465
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:49,367
And when you joined me

466
00:22:49,451 --> 00:22:52,454
to dance while we had
blue paint on our faces.

467
00:22:52,537 --> 00:22:53,455
[Atoy chuckles]

468
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:03,048
[sighs]

469
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:05,175
Master…

470
00:23:05,258 --> 00:23:06,301
Hmm?

471
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:09,471
Can you…

472
00:23:10,597 --> 00:23:14,142
become my official Daddy Atoy?

473
00:23:14,226 --> 00:23:18,688
[sentimental music playing]

474
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:21,525
Oh.

475
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:24,611
Of course.

476
00:23:26,947 --> 00:23:29,032
But wait. How's that?

477
00:23:29,616 --> 00:23:31,701
The name you gave me is too long!

478
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:33,411
Both "Daddy" and "Atoy"!

479
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:36,790
Well, then, I'll call you…

480
00:23:36,873 --> 00:23:37,958
Tatoy!

481
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:41,795
"Tatoy"?

482
00:23:47,926 --> 00:23:49,427
I like the sound of that.

483
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:51,680
[chuckles]

484
00:23:54,724 --> 00:23:58,061
[optimistic music playing]

485
00:23:58,145 --> 00:24:01,231
[sobs] Thank you for everything, Tatoy.

486
00:24:04,568 --> 00:24:06,486
I love you, Tatoy!

487
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:14,452
[sobbing]

488
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,835
I love you too, Ibyang.

489
00:24:32,387 --> 00:24:33,221
‪[music fades]

490
00:24:33,305 --> 00:24:34,514
[electronic blipping]

491
00:24:34,598 --> 00:24:39,186
[tense music playing]

492
00:24:43,940 --> 00:24:46,568
[Cita] She told me
she now calls you Tatoy.

493
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:49,571
Oh, why don't you make it official?

494
00:24:49,654 --> 00:24:50,488
[in English] Official?

495
00:24:50,572 --> 00:24:51,698
Should I adopt her?

496
00:24:51,781 --> 00:24:54,951
I just want to ask forgiveness from you.

497
00:24:55,035 --> 00:24:57,537
I have a surprise for you!

498
00:24:57,621 --> 00:24:59,372
Where did you get those cookies, huh?

499
00:24:59,456 --> 00:25:00,582
‪UP NEXT

500
00:25:00,665 --> 00:25:03,627
A Mrs. Santos approached me.

501
00:25:03,710 --> 00:25:06,171
She was supposed to be
the buyer of their car.

502
00:25:06,254 --> 00:25:09,925
After one week, her husband
was found with his body burned.

503
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:11,801
This is easy. Oh, wait.

504
00:25:11,885 --> 00:25:13,970
Why are you waiting on the street?
Who are you looking for?

505
00:25:14,054 --> 00:25:15,931
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

506
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:18,016
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

507
00:25:18,099 --> 00:25:19,476
♪ <i>One cut</i> ♪

508
00:25:19,559 --> 00:25:21,186
♪ <i>And it's settled</i> ♪

509
00:25:21,269 --> 00:25:22,395
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
